other_tests.findings: Normal left ventricular function at rest, mildly thickened tricuspid aortic valve, mild aortic insufficiency, mild aortic-root dilatation, trivial regurgitation of the other valves; negative for ischemia.
Sinus rhythm at a rate of 78 beats per minute, with probable left ventricular hypertrophy.
Thickening of multiple aortic leaflets but no stenosis, mild-to-moderate aortic insufficiency, normal left ventricular systolic function with an ejection fraction of 60%.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Follow-up echocardiogram showed a persistent mobile density on the aortic valve, although it appeared improved.

other_tests.findings: Echogenic mass on the non-coronary cusp of the aortic valve, consistent with vegetations and moderate aortic insufficiency.
Positive for S. mutans after four days, indicative of bacterial endocarditis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Final positive culture also grew MRSA on fifth hospital day.
